The paper focuses on the design of network protocols for intermittently connected networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also makes use of human behavior and social structure to predict links, which suggests a connection to social networks (cs.SOC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a third-order tensor to organize spatio-temporal aspects of node behavior suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on predicting links in wireless networks suggests a connection to signal processing (cs.SI).
